                            <comment id="14027772" author="tilman" created="Wed, 11 Jun 2014 13:46:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you, I fixed this in rev 1601898 for the trunk and in rev 1601899 for the 1.8 branch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14027838" author="tilman" created="Wed, 11 Jun 2014 14:55:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed files in the 1.8 branch that were catching the exception, in rev 1601920, 1601926, 1601927 1601932, 1601933.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I couldn&apos;t find any code that uses the &quot;new&quot; decryption methods and also brings up a nice error message. If there is, I would insert that everywhere again.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14028410" author="jahewson" created="Wed, 11 Jun 2014 21:21:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In 2.0 InvalidPasswordException extends IOException, which solves the problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
